The '''Sewers of Coruscant''' were a complex of sewers located on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. The sewers were connected to various buildings on Coruscant and had entrances in them, such as the one in [[Xizor's Palace]]. They were heavily guarded by the [[Red Guard]] corps. [[Dianoga/Legends|Dianogas]] inhabited the waters of the sewers. A [[giant dianoga]] was rumored to inhabit one of the main chambers.

Prior to the [[Battle over Coruscant]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], [[Dash Rendar/Legends|Dash Rendar]], [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]], [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]], and [[Benedict Vidkun]] used the sewers to access Xizor's Palace.

==Behind the scenes==
The sewers appear for first time in all the narratives of the [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire|''Shadows of the Empire'']] multimedia project. The [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)|video game]] deviates on the course of events, showing the ''[[Millennium Falcon/Legends|Millennium Falcon]]'' and the ''[[Outrider/Legends|Outrider]]'' flying and landing through the series; then the team splits up throughout the tunnels to look for Leia; Dash Rendar instead places some [[pulse bomb/Legends|pulse bombs]] as a diversion for their escape.

3d artist [[Bill Stoneham]] created 3d concept art for the sewers before their inclusion in the [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)|''Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire'' video game]]. Originally they would be Gothic-like with [[Wikipedia:rib vault|rib vaults]] and Gargoyles, taking inspiration from the sewers of the [[Wikipedia:Phantom of the Opera|''Phantom of the Opera'']].<ref name="secrets">''[[The Secrets of Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire]]'', Part 4: Battle Zones, IV. The Final Battle</ref>

Texture artist [[Chris Hockabout]] was inspired from a boat trip around the dark, mazelike sewers of [[Wikipedia:Prague|Prague]] he took some years earlier.<ref name="secrets" />

